@page "/"

<PageTitle>SpawnDev.ILGPU.ML — Neural Network Inference for .NET</PageTitle>

<div class="hero-section">
    <div class="hero-content">
        <h1 class="hero-title">
            <span class="gradient-text">SpawnDev.ILGPU.ML</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">Neural network inference in C# — no runtime dependencies</p>
        <p class="hero-description">
            GPU-accelerated inference kernels written entirely in C# and transpiled to native compute shaders
            via <a href="https://github.com/LostBeard/SpawnDev.ILGPU" target="_blank">SpawnDev.ILGPU</a>.
            The same code runs in the browser and on desktop across six backends.
            No ONNX Runtime, no JavaScript, no native binaries.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-buttons">
            <a href="getting-started" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
                Get Started
            </a>
            <a href="https://github.com/LostBeard/SpawnDev.ILGPU.ML" target="_blank" class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg">
                GitHub
            </a>
            <a href="benchmark" class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg">
                Benchmark
            </a>
            <a href="inspector" class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg">
                Inspect Model
            </a>
        </div>
        <p class="hero-voice-hint">Try saying "Computer, classify this image" on any demo page &#x1F3A4;</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="features-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">How It Works</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">
        Neural network operations are implemented as
        <a href="https://github.com/m4rs-mt/ILGPU" target="_blank">ILGPU</a> kernels in C#.
        At runtime, SpawnDev.ILGPU transpiles each kernel to the appropriate shader language or binary for the target backend.
    </p>

    <div class="pipeline-visual">
        <div class="pipeline-box pipeline-source">C# Kernel</div>
        <div class="pipeline-arrow"></div>
        <div class="pipeline-box pipeline-compiler">SpawnDev.ILGPU</div>
        <div class="pipeline-arrow"></div>
        <div class="pipeline-targets">
            <span class="pipeline-target target-browser">WGSL</span>
            <span class="pipeline-target target-browser">GLSL</span>
            <span class="pipeline-target target-browser">Wasm</span>
            <span class="pipeline-target target-desktop">PTX</span>
            <span class="pipeline-target target-desktop">OpenCL C</span>
            <span class="pipeline-target target-desktop">CPU</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="features-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Six Backends, One Codebase</h2>

    <h3 class="subsection-title">Browser (Blazor WebAssembly)</h3>
    <div class="features-grid features-grid-3">
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-browser">
            <h3>WebGPU</h3>
            <p>C# kernels transpiled to WGSL compute shaders. Shared memory, barriers, and atomics for tiled matrix multiplication and parallel reductions.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">GPU &mdash; fastest browser path</div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-browser">
            <h3>WebGL</h3>
            <p>Transpiled to GLSL ES 3.0 via Transform Feedback. Works on virtually every browser and device, including mobile and older desktops.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">GPU &mdash; widest compatibility</div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-browser">
            <h3>Wasm</h3>
            <p>Compiled to native WebAssembly binary and dispatched to Web Workers. Full shared memory and barrier support for parallel CPU inference.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">CPU &mdash; universal fallback</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="subsection-title">Desktop (Console, WPF, ASP.NET)</h3>
    <div class="features-grid features-grid-3">
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-desktop">
            <h3>CUDA</h3>
            <p>Direct PTX compilation for NVIDIA GPUs. Maximum throughput with full hardware access.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">NVIDIA GPU</div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-desktop">
            <h3>OpenCL</h3>
            <p>Cross-vendor GPU compute. Runs on NVIDIA, AMD, and Intel GPUs and integrated graphics.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">Any GPU</div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card feature-highlight-desktop">
            <h3>CPU</h3>
            <p>Multi-threaded CPU accelerator. Useful for debugging, headless servers, and machines without a GPU.</p>
            <div class="feature-tag">Debug and fallback</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="features-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Implemented Operations</h2>
    <div class="features-grid features-grid-3">
        <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Matrix Multiplication</h3>
            <p>Tiled 16x16 with shared memory. Batched variant for multi-head attention. Auto-falls back to simple kernel on backends without shared memory.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Convolution</h3>
            <p>Conv2D with arbitrary kernel size, stride, and padding. ConvTranspose2D for upsampling. Used for patch embedding and DPT head refinement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Normalization</h3>
            <p>Row-wise LayerNorm with learned gamma and beta parameters. Two-pass numerically stable Softmax for attention score computation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Activations</h3>
            <p>GELU, ReLU, Sigmoid, Tanh, SiLU, LeakyReLU, HardSigmoid, HardSwish, ELU — with in-place variants to minimize allocations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>71 ONNX Operators</h3>
            <p>Full operator registry supporting classification, depth estimation, style transfer, super resolution, and more. Direct .onnx file loading with zero-dependency protobuf parser.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Preprocessing Toolkit</h3>
            <p>Image decode, color conversion, EXIF orientation, audio FFT + mel spectrogram, BPE tokenizer, YOLO NMS, depth colormaps — all built in.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="features-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">Roadmap</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">
        SpawnDev.ILGPU.ML is being developed toward a complete cross-platform inference engine.
    </p>
    <div class="roadmap-grid">
        <div class="roadmap-item done">
            <div class="roadmap-status">Done</div>
            <div class="roadmap-label">Cross-backend migration (all 6 backends)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="roadmap-item done">
            <div class="roadmap-status">Done</div>
            <div class="roadmap-label">PlaywrightMultiTest (356 tests across 6 backends)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="roadmap-item done">
            <div class="roadmap-status">Done</div>
            <div class="roadmap-label">Tensor abstraction, buffer pool, graph compiler</div>
        </div>
        <div class="roadmap-item done">
            <div class="roadmap-status">Done</div>
            <div class="roadmap-label">71 ONNX operators + InferenceSession API</div>
        </div>
        <div class="roadmap-item done">
            <div class="roadmap-status">Done</div>
